definition.value: A luteolin glucosiduronic acid consisting of luteolin having a beta-D-glucosiduronic acid residue attached at the 7-position.
An optically active form of 2-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid having (S)-configuration.
A beta-diketone that is acetylacetone in which a 4-hydroxyphenyl group and a 2,4-dihydroxyphenyl group replace the two methyl groups.
The phosphate of choline; and the parent compound of the phosphocholine family.
